p: The pattern of Zika virus NT appeared very similar with samples of the naïve and pre-immune groups ( Fig 11A); reminiscent of what was observed in IgM ELISA ( Fig 10A). However, statistical analysis revealed again significantly lower titers by a factor of 1.83 in the pre-immune group ( Fig 11A). Consistent with the pool data ( Fig 8B and S9 Fig), neutralization of dengue virus was observed with almost all samples from the pre-immune group, whereas most of the samples from the naïve group were negative ( Fig 11B).
